label.value: cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of the population in the embryonic placenta.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development

definition.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development.

label.value: coreceptor activity involved in epidermal growth factor receptor signaling pathway

definition.value: Combining with an extracellular messenger, and in cooperation with a primary EGF receptor, initiating a change in cell activity through the EGF receptor signaling pathway.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in mammary gland duct elongation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of mammary gland branch epithelial cells, resulting in the elongation of the branch. The mammary gland branch differs from the bud in that it is not the initial curved portion of the outgrowth.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

definition.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: positive regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

definition.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: negative regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

definition.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of mesenchymal cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: regulation of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in tissue homeostasis

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation resulting in the maintenance of a steady-state number of cells within a tissue.

label.value: positive regulation of meiosis I

definition.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of meiosis I, a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the first phase of meiosis, in which cells divide and homologous chromosomes are paired and segregated from each other, producing two daughter cells.

label.value: regulation of DNA replication initiation involved in plasmid copy number maintenance

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of initiation of plasmid DNA replication that contributes to copy number maintenance.

label.value: negative regulation of DNA replication initiation involved in plasmid copy number maintenance

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of initiation of plasmid DNA replication that contributes to copy number maintenance.

label.value: mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in lung development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a mesenchymal cell population that contributes to the progression of the lung over time. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label.value: phospholipase D inhibitor activity

definition.value: Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a phospholipase D, an enzyme that catalyzes the reaction -  a phosphatidylcholine + H2O -eq- choline + a phosphatidate.

label.value: lipid tube

definition.value: A macromolecular complex that contains a tube of lipid surrounded by a protein coat.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in kidney morphogenesis

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation that contributes to the shaping of the kidney.

label.value: endopeptidase activator activity

definition.value: Increases the activity of an endopeptidase, any enzyme that hydrolyzes nonterminal peptide bonds in polypeptides.

label.value: peptidase regulator activity

definition.value: Modulates the activity of a peptidase, any enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis peptide bonds.

label.value: endopeptidase regulator activity

definition.value: Modulates the activity of a peptidase, any enzyme that hydrolyzes nonterminal peptide bonds in polypeptides.

label.value: type I terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary to release neurotransmitters that will induce the contraction of muscle. The axon terminus is considered to be the whole region of thickening and the terminal bouton is a specialized region of it.

label.value: type II terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a non-glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary to release neurotransmitters at a regulatory synapse. The axon terminus is considered to be the whole region of thickening and the terminal bouton is a specialized region of it.

label.value: type Ib terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary for the tonic release neurotransmitters that will induce the contraction of muscle. Type Ib terminal boutons are larger than type Is terminal boutons.

label.value: type Is terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary for the phasic release neurotransmitters that will induce the contraction of muscle. Type Is terminal boutons are smaller than type Ib terminal boutons.

label.value: clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle

definition.value: A clathrin-sculpted lipid bilayer membrane-enclosed vesicle after clathrin release and containing gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle.

label.value: clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle lumen

definition.value: The volume enclosed by the membrane of the clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle.

label.value: clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle membrane

definition.value: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in mesonephros development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of the population in the mesonephros.

label.value: mesonephric mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in mesonephros development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a mesonephric mesenchymal cell population.

label.value: mesonephric extraglomerular mesangial cell proliferation involved in mesonephros development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of extraglomerular glomerular mesangium cells in the mesonephros by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. Extraglomerular mesangial cells (also known as lacis cells, Goormaghtigh cells) are light-staining cells in the kidney found outside the glomerulus, near the vascular pole and macula densa.

label.value: mesonephric glomerular mesangial cell proliferation involved in mesonephros development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of glomerular mesangial cells in the mesonephros, resulting in the expansion of the population.

label.value: mesonephric intraglomerular mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of intraglomerular glomerular mesangium cells in the mesonephros by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. Intraglomerular mesangial cells are specialized pericytes located among the glomerular capillaries within a renal corpuscle of a kidney. They are required for filtration, structural support and phagocytosis.

label.value: canonical Wnt signaling pathway involved in positive regulation of cardiac muscle cell proliferation

definition.value: The canonical Wnt signaling pathway that contributes to an expansion of the population of cardiac muscle cells.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in heart morphogenesis

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

label.value: canonical Wnt signaling pathway involved in positive regulation of cardiac outflow tract cell proliferation

definition.value: The canonical Wnt signaling pathway that contributes to the modulation of the expansion of a population of cardiac outflow tract cells.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in outflow tract morphogenesis

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the outflow tract.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in Malpighian tubule morphogenesis

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population and contributing to the shaping of a Malpighian tubule.

label.value: neural precursor cell proliferation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of neural precursor cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. A neural precursor cell is either a nervous system stem cell or a nervous system progenitor cell.

label.value: fibroblast proliferation involved in heart morphogenesis

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of fibroblasts, resulting in the expansion of a fibroblast population that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

label.value: integral component of muscle cell projection membrane

definition.value: The component of the muscle cell projection membrane consisting of the gene products that have some part that penetrates at least one leaflet of the membrane bilayer. This component includes gene products that are buried in the bilayer with no exposure outside the bilayer.

label.value: L-arginine transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the stereospecific transfer of L-arginine, 2-amino-5-guanidinopentanoic acid, across a biological membrane.

label.value: O-acetyl-ADP-ribose deacetylase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction O-acetyl-ADP-ribose + H2O -eq- ADP-ribose + acetate.

label.value: plasma membrane part of cell-substrate junction.

definition.value: The part of the plasma membrane that contributes to the structure of a cell-substrate junction.

label.value: plasma membrane part of hemidesmosome

definition.value: The part of the plasma membrane that contributes to the structure of a hemidesmosome.

label.value: plasma membrane part of cell junction

definition.value: The part of the plasma membrane that contributes to the structure of a cell junction.

label.value: karyomere

definition.value: A membrane-bound intermediate cleavage-stage structure of individual or groups of chromosomes that coalesces and fuses with other karyomeres to form a nucleus during interphase. Karyomere formation occurs in blastomeres undergoing rapid cell division.

label.value: regulation of type B pancreatic cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of type B pancreatic cell proliferation.

label.value: karyomere assembly

definition.value: The process where the nuclear membrane engulfs condensed chromosomes to form karyomeres during M phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: karyomere membrane fusion

definition.value: Process whereby karyomere membranes fuse during interphase to form a single lobed nucleus.
